remarks: "Felapton", one of the syllogisms of Aristotelian logic.  No ` ph ` is ` ps ` , all ` ph ` is ` ch ` , and some ` ph ` exist, therefore some ` ch ` is not ` ps ` .  (In Aristotelian notation, EAO-3:  MeP and MaS therefore SoP.) For example, "No flowers are animals" and "All flowers are plants", therefore "Some plants are not animals".  (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 28-Aug-2016.)  (Revised by David A. Wheeler, 2-Sep-2016.)
statement:
felapton.maj $e |- A. x ( ph -> -. ps ) $.
felapton.min $e |- A. x ( ph -> ch ) $.
felapton.e $e |- E. x ph $.
felapton $p |- E. x ( ch /\ -. ps ) $.
